snippet.textDisplay:
I'm Spanish so a black wedding dress is completely normal. It's to symbolize the fact that you will be with your husband "till death do you part". Yes, Roman Catholic black wedding dresses.
My mother even brought out the head piece that had been in our family over a hundred years. I had no idea it still even existed!
Then I dared to ask something I wanted my grandmother's wedding dress from 1945 "duchess satin" which cost 100$ then. My mother's wedding dress custom made in 1977 to be in my dress.....but how?
I found a company that will take fabric pieces that are from your family's wedding dresses and place them carefully into your dress. This way it won't be obvious to the world but you will know.
I never thought my mother would say yes to my idea....but she did.
My dress will carry the love of dead Grandmother and my still living mother.
